<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>赛琪 |关于人类状况</title><link>https://psyche.co</link><description>Psyche 是 Aeon 的一本数字杂志，通过心理学、哲学和艺术阐明人类状况。</description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 09 Nov 2023 06:14:16 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>如何帮助您的孩子上学</title><link>https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-help-your-child-overcome-reluctance-to-attend-school?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="透过窗户可以看到沙发上的一个女人和一个男孩正在严肃地交谈" src="https://nu.aeon.co/images/340b776b-6f6a-4ed5-a250-1bf95da266b5/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;您的孩子早上是否焦虑、不愿意出门？这是一个富有同情心的计划，旨在帮助他们重返校园&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——安娜·斯莫特、格伦·梅尔文和玛丽·叶&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-help-your-child-overcome-reluctance-to-attend-school?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Nov 2023 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-help-your-child-overcome-reluctance-to-attend-school?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>哺乳动物的同性性行为是为了维持和平而进化的</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/same-sex-sexual-behaviour-in-mammals-evolved-to-keep-the-peace?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="不明确的" src="https://omicron.aeon.co/images/65787e46-1f5b-4e8a-9959-ffef60e55466/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;尽管这些新发现不能告诉我们太多关于人类性行为的信息，但它们可以帮助解决进化悖论&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——莎拉·爱&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/same-sex-sexual-behaviour-in-mammals-evolved-to-keep-the-peace?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Nov 2023 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/same-sex-sexual-behaviour-in-mammals-evolved-to-keep-the-peace?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>为什么我们对 TikTok 上的心理健康视频充满希望</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/why-were-hopeful-about-mental-health-videos-on-tiktok?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="一名男子在摄像机前呈现剪影，并被环形灯照亮" src="https://omicron.aeon.co/images/626f3c9c-b72e-4513-bf7d-6aef34d1d05d/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;人们在 TikTok 上传播自己的心理自我诊断。一些专家感到担忧，但我们看到了机会&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;- 艾略特法学家和朱莉娅法学家&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/why-were-hopeful-about-mental-health-videos-on-tiktok?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 06 Nov 2023 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/why-were-hopeful-about-mental-health-videos-on-tiktok?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>饭纲博览会</title><link>https://psyche.co/films/get-lost-in-enigmatic-memories-of-a-small-town-japanese-fair?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://epsilon.aeon.co/images/b881593e-78e7-4d24-8d63-15b72177a25e/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;这部引人入胜的动画唤起了模糊的记忆和徒劳的遗憾，讲述了一个在日本陷入沉思的男人的故事&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;- 心灵电影&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/films/get-lost-in-enigmatic-memories-of-a-small-town-japanese-fair?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;观看 Psyche&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Nov 2023 10:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/films/get-lost-in-enigmatic-memories-of-a-small-town-japanese-fair?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>为什么口语诗不仅仅是诗歌朗诵</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/why-spoken-word-poetry-is-so-much-more-than-a-poetry-reading?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="一名男子在俱乐部活动中打手势并背诵诗歌" src="https://nu.aeon.co/images/c67db614-97f2-4de7-8d29-4afa6700ee6e/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;随着诗歌回归其作为表演艺术的根源，它为许多人提供了强大的治疗和社区来源&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——艾丽卡·弗莱彻&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/why-spoken-word-poetry-is-so-much-more-than-a-poetry-reading?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Nov 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/why-spoken-word-poetry-is-so-much-more-than-a-poetry-reading?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>如何在“冒名顶替综合症”中茁壮成长</title><link>https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-move-beyond-imposter-syndrome-and-thrive?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="通勤者冲过静止的通勤列车。火车窗外倒映着悉尼海港大桥" src="https://epsilon.aeon.co/images/8906f346-e0b0-4d66-8002-bf2466c36e93/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;对自己无能和不值得的担忧可能会阻碍你。尝试以下步骤，迈向你想要的生活&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——吉尔·斯托达德&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-move-beyond-imposter-syndrome-and-thrive?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Nov 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-move-beyond-imposter-syndrome-and-thrive?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>异教是爱尔兰保护运动的强大力量</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/paganism-is-a-potent-force-in-irelands-conservation-movement?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="不明确的" src="https://nu.aeon.co/images/16ea5cf4-8079-40f9-8992-bce29f5b68f8/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;长期以来对愤怒仙女居住的“另一个世界”的信仰现在正在推动爱尔兰生态活动的复兴&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;- 朱朱巷&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/paganism-is-a-potent-force-in-irelands-conservation-movement?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 31 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/paganism-is-a-potent-force-in-irelands-conservation-movement?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>聆听恐怖：为什么许多女性喜欢真实犯罪播客</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/listening-in-on-horror-why-many-women-love-true-crime-podcasts?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="雨夜，一位表情沉思的女士在公交车上听耳机" src="https://alpha.aeon.co/images/d6d41d21-ed65-4357-a882-78dbf57e48bb/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;真实犯罪播客将针对女性的暴力行为变成了一种娱乐形式。为什么这么多女性听众喜欢它们？&lt;p&gt; &lt;em&gt;——阿米莉亚·安东尼&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/listening-in-on-horror-why-many-women-love-true-crime-podcasts?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 30 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/listening-in-on-horror-why-many-women-love-true-crime-podcasts?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>心依然嗡嗡作响</title><link>https://psyche.co/films/stories-of-mothers-in-crisis-form-a-poignant-portrait-of-unconditional-love?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://epsilon.aeon.co/images/706a0e80-e38b-43ab-ad6e-8c9edf1db1a4/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;温柔地审视五位面临巨大困难的母亲，她们开始打破毒瘾、贫困和忽视的循环&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;- 心灵电影&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/films/stories-of-mothers-in-crisis-form-a-poignant-portrait-of-unconditional-love?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;观看 Psyche&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Oct 2023 10:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/films/stories-of-mothers-in-crisis-form-a-poignant-portrait-of-unconditional-love?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>在充满尼安德特人骨骼的洞穴中挖掘答案</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/digging-for-answers-in-a-cave-filled-with-neanderthal-skeletons?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="在洞穴地面上挖掘的浮雕中可以看到头骨的骨骼轮廓" src="https://omicron.aeon.co/images/9ed85d80-8a3d-44e1-a3db-128c02bb1398/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;当一组研究人员返回一个被认为是尼安德特人埋葬地的伊拉克洞穴时，他们发现了以下内容&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——莎拉·爱&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/digging-for-answers-in-a-cave-filled-with-neanderthal-skeletons?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/digging-for-answers-in-a-cave-filled-with-neanderthal-skeletons?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item></channel></rss>